Content:
@Parliament Member For MPs, you guys can motion any Bills, but Bills are chosen by @G CAT to be voted on. There are three slots for bills that could be implemented per session week. Once voted on into the slots, the Parliament members work on the bills through writing down scenarios to increase success modifier. The bills can be replaced from each of the slots and replaced with a new one depending on if the parliament wants to call a re-vote. But once the Bills are implemented, it cannot be revoked. The only one to revoke it is the Supreme Justice.

Flow:
Propose Bills>Vote On Bills to Slot>Work on Bills>Implement Bills
